document.body:
jess3 blogs, U.S. entrants OneWorld (C) and Team Dennis Conner (R) try to get to the finish line in light wind past the Noises Islands during their Flight 5 match trailed by Swiss entrant Alinghi, who was racing Britain's GBR Challenge, on race day four of Round Robin Two on Auckland's Hauraki Gulf in New Zealand, October 30, 2002. The OneWorld race was abandoned due to not being able to finish the last leg within the allocated 45 minutes, however Alinghi recorded a win over GBR. OneWorld, are one of nine syndicates competing in the Louis Vuitton Cup which started October 1, the winner of which will race Team New Zealand for the America's Cup in February 2003. REUTERS/Nigel Marple
